Description: Handle of Knidian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp
Type series: KT1240 (in Grace's unpublished Knidian Type series)
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p. 26,4. Name Timoxenos. There is a wide choice for the lost name of the eponym.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0321)
